metadata.name: Subdivision Squares #46
metadata.description:
This is an original Op Art piece that incorporates an algorithm for drawing alternating black and white concentric squares inside a space defined by of another algorithm that divides the picture space in half (alternatively vertically or horizontally) on consecutive iterations. A coin-toss algorithm decides which half to fill with concentric squares and the other half is further divided in half again. The subdivision process iterates until the half space is too small to draw squares in.

Check out Dr. Bill Generative Art OG website @ drbillkolomyjec.com

metadata.name: simple things #125
metadata.description:
There‚Äôs beauty in simple things. Sunlight. A reflection on a puddle. The flight of a bird. Observing the clouds. Spending time with loved ones.

To celebrate the re-opening of fxhash, I'd like to contribute with some simple thing to enjoy among friends who rejoin after some time.

Simple things is a piece that is just that: simple things. Nothing fancy here. Simple circles doing simple movement, with simple colours. Maybe the viewer will rejoice in observing them transit on the screen.

It has some controls: you can press ‚Äús‚Äù to save a png file. You can set a higher resolution pressing ‚Äúd‚Äù followed by 1-9 to increase pixel density (if you get a black image, press ‚Äúd 0‚Äù and start again with a lower number). Simple controls.

It has also colour controls: press z for brightness, x for contrast, g for gamma, b for blur, n for noise followed by + or - to alter their values. You might get some simple variations that you might enjoy. Press a to enable/disable all colour controls (except the noise).

The pieces exhibit simple variations: palettes, circle sizes, density of elements, backgrounds. The colours might be inverted sometimes. The direction of the movement changes also in some pieces. Some are grayscale pieces.

Just like in life, enjoying simple things is sometimes enough to leave behind the noise and our worries. Also like in life, if one wants something extra, they may get it by looking for it...

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodr√≠guez, @msoriaro.
Made in p5.js, and glsl for the image controls.

metadata.name: A24Z #345
metadata.description:
Every artist and collector feels the joy of both creating and collecting. But if I could share the joy of creating with collectors. And collectors with their family and friends, what may be an additive process of joy is now perhaps exponential. Joy to the power of 26 to be exact. 

In this work I invite my friends and collectors to collaborate with me. Though not in coding, but together in a process of creating narratives and visuals. Code and story. We didn‚Äôt use github, just a simple p5.js editor to try out different programs and palettes. Pedrofe and J0rdan pick their palettes tastefully and carefully. okeoke, perhaps more of a genius than he lets on, picks his palettes blind. No hex color picker. Just straight up rhymes.  

In our discussions verbal language was forbidden. Only emojis were allowed to express our tastes and views. Each emojis put down on google doc was taken with absolutely seriousness. 

Pedro: Loves to taking his daily walks on ‚ÄúMagic Mushroom Mountain‚Äù

J0rdan: Wonders about ‚ÄúQuark Question Quiches‚Äù

Okeoke: Just get lost in ‚ÄúFinnegans‚Äô Flower Fields.‚Äù

It has been a great joy to present our illustration book A24Z, 8 more than you know who. Each page expresses the alphabet with the best of our knowledge in semantics and sarcasm. Collect just 1 page, collect the alphabets that spell out your name, collect the whole A to Z. Read it to your children or loved ones. Though you might need to interpolate or extrapolate with great imagination which children all have. But most importantly, like all children, have fun!

Press 1 to save png, only for Chrome, not Safari. Preview images are compressed or broken, test capture at 300 sec.

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: FairyCells II #148
metadata.description:
FairyCells II is intended as a logical continuation of the first FairyCells series. By dropping the plotter drawing constraint, new perspectives for exploration appeared.
This is how these cells began to intertwine, live together, mutate and change color, like an evolving system.

What surprises me the most in this new series, is the stories appearing behind each new composition. See how these abstracts shapes can come to life and narrate us things through our imagination.

Each color palette takes us into a different world, drawing a very specific atmosphere.

As me, let yourself be carried away by these stories üí´ !

Artwork by Julien_Espagnon, 2022.

Control : Press ¬´ S ¬ª to save the image as a PNG.

metadata.name: a manifested realization #117
metadata.description:
In general, this piece continues my study of procedural abstract expressionism. However, I've developed a new small bit of code I am testing here; I am trying to create a "clumping" noise function that looks natural but doesn't have the obvious "look" of Perlin noise, and is more controllable. This piece contains my first public use of this. So it is, in a way, a test. 

I was inspired by the IRL paintings of Francesco D'Adamo, specifically his "Manifesti" series, although (as is the way of things) the end result looks nothing like what I started with, and is a more general 1950s abstract expressionism look. 

This piece is a gift to the collectors of all my recent "a" mints. Thank you all!

metadata.name: Pipeline #6
metadata.description:
The only way to deal with an unfree world is to become so absolutely free that your very existence is an act of rebellion. 
[Albert Camus]

I imagined a pipeline that runs within the limits of a three-dimensional cube. Each segment takes an arbitrary direction from time to time, careful not to cross the limits and not to occupy non-free spaces.
It can happen, quite rarely, that the pipeline has no more spaces available... and then the iteration stops, giving rise to a relatively simple structure.
You can follow the pipeline path by interactively manipulating the point of view.

metadata.name: Agents 2.0 #330
metadata.description:
There are more than thousand agents(random). These agents can move in any direction. I have given 3 types of direction. First is single(together) direction, second is multi(against) direction and the last is "No Movement(Direction)". Agents have their  own speed, size, movement smoothness, and turbulence. The art is programmatically drawn using basic shapes, math, random using p5js.

All the agents walks around 100 to 230 steps. All speed, smoothness, waviness, turbulence, size, direction, color are randomly generated.

In this art, I am using 29 color palettes. these palettes are from: https://ronikaufman.github.io/color_pals/

Press s or 'S' to save image in default quality.
Add scale=print& before fxhash in the URL to save image in high quality.
Add scale=print2& before fxhash in the URL to save image in highest quality.

Example:
Before: https://gateway.fxhash2.xyz/ipfs/QmYiErKegzf66TgVB...../?fxhash=ooXFx4Cbn23Sacb...
After: https://gateway.fxhash2.xyz/ipfs/QmYiErKegzf66TgVB...../?scale=print&fxhash=ooXFx4Cbn23Sacb... 

Note: Art can take some minutes to render.

Art: 8/2/2022
Created By: ArtLife
Twitter: https://twitter.com/iamPraveenIN

metadata.name: Logical Interaction #8
metadata.description:
Neo-minimalist composition that symbolizes the unequivocal interaction of organisms for an exchange of information and understanding between them. However, these interactions also generate clashes, rejections, discards. Everything will always depend on the needs of each entity, because the search for coupling sometimes becomes an exhaustive and extensive activity.





Created using purespider/fxhash-pfp.
